Preprocessing by SNV and derivation

julia> model1 = snv()
Jchemo.JchemoModel{typeof(snv), Base.Pairs{Symbol, Union{}, Tuple{}, @NamedTuple{}}}(Jchemo.snv, nothing, Base.Pairs{Symbol, Union{}, Tuple{}, @NamedTuple{}}())

julia> model2 = savgol(npoint = 21, deriv = 2, degree = 3)
Jchemo.JchemoModel{typeof(savgol), Base.Pairs{Symbol, Int64, Tuple{Symbol, Symbol, Symbol}, @NamedTuple{npoint::Int64, deriv::Int64, degree::Int64}}}(Jchemo.savgol, nothing, Base.Pairs(:npoint => 21, :deriv => 2, :degree => 3))

julia> model = pip(model1, model2) ;

julia> fit!(model, X)

julia> Xp = transf(model, X) ;

Split Train/Test from Tot

julia> s = Bool.(test) ; # same as: s = Y.test .== 1

julia> Xtrain = rmrow(Xp, s) ;

julia> typtrain = rmrow(typ, s) ;

julia> Xtest = Xp[s, :] ;

julia> typtest = typ[s] ;

julia> ntrain = nro(Xtrain) ;

julia> ntest = nro(Xtest) ;

julia> (ntot = ntot, ntrain, ntest)
(ntot = 4075, ntrain = 3701, ntest = 374)

Umap on Train

julia> nlv = 3
3

julia> n_neighbors = 40 ; min_dist = .4
0.4

julia> model = umap(; nlv, n_neighbors, min_dist)
       #model = umap(; nlv, n_neighbors, min_dist, psamp = .5)  # faster but less accurate
Jchemo.JchemoModel{typeof(umap), Base.Pairs{Symbol, Real, Tuple{Symbol, Symbol, Symbol}, @NamedTuple{nlv::Int64, n_neighbors::Int64, min_dist::Float64}}}(Jchemo.umap, nothing, Base.Pairs{Symbol, Real, Tuple{Symbol, Symbol, Symbol}, @NamedTuple{nlv::Int64, n_neighbors::Int64, min_dist::Float64}}(:nlv => 3, :n_neighbors => 40, :min_dist => 0.4))

julia> fit!(model, Xtrain)

julia> @head T = model.fitm.T
